{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F11tUysSj1RmGZUoadcHbU","type":"tool_result","content":"   155→  - For host script steps: contents of a referenced script file under `.cloche/scripts/` (text files only); the content panel is hidden when no displayable content is available\n   156→  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n   157→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n   158→\n   159→### DAG rendering\n   160→Client-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\n   161→layers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\n   162→heuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\n   163→left-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n   164→\n   165→Non-success wires (any result not in `success`, `ok`, `done`, `pass`) are offset\n   166→vertically below the main flow so they don't overlap the happy-path edges. These wires\n   167→use a distinct failure color and reduced opacity (`dag-edge-nonsuccess` class) with a\n   168→matching arrowhead marker.\n   169→\n   170→When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\n   171→collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\n   172→which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. Non-success wires within a merge bus\n   173→are offset to their own vertical positions, and the collector line extends to cover them.\n   174→This reduces wire clutter as graphs grow in complexity.\n   175→\n   176→The DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n   177→\n   178→### API additions\n   179→\n   180→```\n   181→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n   182→```\n   183→\n   184→Response:\n   185→```json\n   186→[\n   187→  {\n   188→    \"name\": \"develop\",\n   189→    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n   190→    \"location\": \"container\",\n   191→    \"steps\": [\n   192→      {\n   193→        \"name\": \"implement\",\n   194→        \"type\": \"agent\","}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b76d9e4-3e18-44aa-b9db-75bc283939a4","uuid":"aceaa72f-ea18-4f14-a940-d2fa5a434a5e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md","content":"  - For host script steps: contents of a referenced script file under `.cloche/scripts/` (text files only); the content panel is hidden when no displayable content is available\n  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n\n### DAG rendering\nClient-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\nlayers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\nheuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\nleft-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n\nNon-success wires (any result not in `success`, `ok`, `done`, `pass`) are offset\nvertically below the main flow so they don't overlap the happy-path edges. These wires\nuse a distinct failure color and reduced opacity (`dag-edge-nonsuccess` class) with a\nmatching arrowhead marker.\n\nWhen multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ncollector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\nwhich feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. Non-success wires within a merge bus\nare offset to their own vertical positions, and the collector line extends to cover them.\nThis reduces wire clutter as graphs grow in complexity.\n\nThe DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n\n### API additions\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n```\n\nResponse:\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"develop\",\n    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n    \"location\": \"container\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"implement\",\n        \"type\": \"agent\",","numLines":40,"startLine":155,"totalLines":234}}}
